:INFO
What Vinegar Actually Is
Vinegar is the result of acetic acid bacteria (AAB) converting alcohol into \
acetic acid. You need a liquid with 5 to 12 percent alcohol, a mother culture \
(or raw unfiltered vinegar to inoculate from), and oxygen. The process takes \
4 to 8 weeks depending on temperature and surface area.

